Toolbar now has grey background again.
Bug Fix: On Linux (Mint) password prompt dialog was missing the title. Setting shell to null fixed it.

Added logging. Investigating why app doesn't come up maximized after being maximized and closed and re-opened.

No longer build source code .zip file as source code is in GitHub.

MESSAGE.value:
Version 0.83
Updated Ant build scripts to point to cached modules on my new machine.

With the 4.35 Eclipse jars, which are signed, caused problems building the app from the IDE (to test and debug).
The Ant scripts stripped out the signing data.
Solution was to copy all the jars to an "unsigned" folder, and then strip out the signing data:
find . -name '*.jar' -exec zip -d '{}' 'META-INF/*.SF' ';'
(https://stackoverflow.com/questions/7757083/how-do-i-unsign-a-jar)
Updated README.md

Version 0.84
Text Background Color is now in a distinct tab in the Settings dialog.
The outline item's color is only used if it also has a font. By default, when an outline item is stored, a color of black is saved. But the color is only relevant if a font was specified. Specifying a font is the only way to specify the color of an outline item.
Now update an item's background and foreground when a new item is rendered.

Version 0.84
Updated copyright notices.

Version 0.84
If an outline item with a specified font was selected, changing the background color didn't take effect until it was re-rendered.

On Linux, user can now specify the default font color.
